<div id="review_3768502134" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3768502134" />
    <a title="Kyo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18461352-kyo"><img alt="Kyo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1456580535p2/18461352.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3768502134?book_show_action=true">Jan 13, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kyo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kyo" href="/user/show/18461352-kyo">Kyo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780374526160" href="/book/show/81865.Ph_dre">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3768502134" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3882316998539761572">After reading the original French, I think I appreciated Hughes&apos;s translation even more, because–as always–he is a master in both retaining the original while also bringing something new to the words! The story itself is a masterful adaptation of the myth, delving even deeper into feelings of anger, jealousy, remorse (and the more negative side of love in general) than Euripides&apos; orginal (which is also amazing).<br/><br/>Anyway, if you&apos;re looking for an amazing translation and version of Racine and Euripi</span>
  <span id="freeText3882316998539761572" style="display:none">After reading the original French, I think I appreciated Hughes's translation even more, because–as always–he is a master in both retaining the original while also bringing something new to the words! The story itself is a masterful adaptation of the myth, delving even deeper into feelings of anger, jealousy, remorse (and the more negative side of love in general) than Euripides' orginal (which is also amazing).<br /><br />Anyway, if you're looking for an amazing translation and version of Racine and Euripides (respectively), I'd definitely recommend this one!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3882316998539761572" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


